    {
      "@id": "deribit:id",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Id",
      "rdfs:comment": "Unique identifier"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:book_state",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Book State",
      "rdfs:comment": "The state of the order book. Represents the current lifecycle stage of the instrument.\n\n**State Lifecycle and Meanings:**\n\n- `open`: Default state for running books. In this state book is accepting new orders, edits, cancels; prices should be updated, trading is live.\n- `settlement`: Books enters to this state during settlement/delivery. New orders, edits, cancels are not accepted. After this state normally next state should be `open` if it was settlement, or `delivered` if it was delivery. On enter to this state good till day orders in book are canceled.\n- `delivered`: Final state of book that has been delivered. New orders, edits, cancels are not accepted. After some time book process will be terminated and, instrument moved to `expired_instruments` and its `instrument_state` will become archivized. On enter to this all open orders in book are canceled.\n- `inactive`: After a book is deactivated, this state is set on book. New orders, edits, cancels are not accepted. On enter to this all open orders in book are canceled. Book in this state is not considered as open. This can be also final state for book.\n- `locked`: New orders, edits, are not accepted, only cancels ARE accepted. In some cases when configured books can start as locked or it may become locked on admin request. Settlement is possible on locked books.\n- `halted`: The state that books enter as a result of an error. Settlement is not possible when there is at least one book in this state.\n- `archivized`: Set when instrument is moved to `expired_instruments` table, final state.\n"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:greeks",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Greeks",
      "rdfs:comment": "Only for options. Greeks are risk measures that describe how the option's price changes with respect to various factors.\n\n**Delta (\u0394)**\n\nDeribit uses two different Deltas:\n- **DeltaTotal** in the account summary uses the **Net Transaction Delta (NTD)**\n- **Delta** for individual option expiries is the **Black Scholes Delta**\n\nIn the settings section you can toggle Net Transaction Delta instead.\n\n**What is DeltaTotal in the account summary?**\n`DeltaTotal = Net Transaction Delta of options + BTC Position of Futures`\n\n**What is Net Transaction Delta?**\n`Net Transaction Delta = Black Scholes Delta - Mark Price of Options`\n\n**Why do we use a Net Transaction Delta?**\nThe Delta Total uses the Net Transaction Delta (or price adjusted Delta) of the options. This is because, from a risk perspective, we are interested in the change in Bitcoin price as the underlying changes.\n\nYou should actually treat your delta as **Equity + Delta Total** if you want to have less risk for your USD PnL.\n\n**Example:** Consider a call option with strike 0, which has a Black Scholes Delta of 1 and Net Transaction Delta = 0.\n\nImagine you have 2 BTC equity and no positions and BTC price is at USD 60k. In that case you would short 2 Futures contracts to hedge your USD exposure to BTC.\n\nNow let's say you buy one call with strike 0. The question is if you should sell another future?\n\nThe call will always have a price of 1 BTC. So you buy it at 1 BTC which equates to USD 60k. Let's say the price increases to USD 70k. The value of the call is still 1 BTC. At settlement you receive 1 BTC for the call. So you paid 1 BTC and then receive 1 BTC which means your USD PnL on buying the call is 0. If you sold a future on it, then you would actually lose on the future.\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f **During the 30 minute settlement period we decay your Delta.** See [Delta decay during settlement](https://support.deribit.com/hc/en-us/articles/25944751433757-Delta-decay-during-settlement) for more details.\n\n**Theta (\u0398)**\n\nThe Theta that Deribit uses is the **minimum of (1 day Theta, lifetime theta of the option)**. So if you take an option with 1 hour to expire for example, generally Black Scholes Theta will give you the equivalent 1 day Theta. Whereas we show the 1 hour Theta, so our Theta would differ from Black Scholes Theta when time to expiry is less than 1 day.\n\n**Vega, Gamma, and Rho**\n\nVega (not actually a Greek symbol), Gamma, Theta and Rho values shown on Deribit are calculated using **standard Black Scholes without adjustments**.\n"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:greeks_delta",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Delta",
      "rdfs:comment": "(Only for option) The delta value for the option. This is the **Black Scholes Delta** for individual option expiries. \n\nNote that DeltaTotal in account summary uses Net Transaction Delta instead. See the greeks object description for more details.\n",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:greeks"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:greeks_gamma",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Gamma",
      "rdfs:comment": "(Only for option) The gamma value for the option. Calculated using standard Black Scholes without adjustments.\n\nGamma measures the rate of change of delta with respect to changes in the underlying asset price.\n",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:greeks"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:greeks_rho",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Rho",
      "rdfs:comment": "(Only for option) The rho value for the option. Calculated using standard Black Scholes without adjustments.\n\nRho measures the sensitivity of the option price to changes in the risk-free interest rate.\n",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:greeks"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:greeks_theta",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Theta",
      "rdfs:comment": "(Only for option) The theta value for the option. Deribit uses the **minimum of (1 day Theta, lifetime theta of the option)**.\n\nSo if you take an option with 1 hour to expire for example, generally Black Scholes Theta will give you the equivalent 1 day Theta. Whereas we show the 1 hour Theta, so our Theta would differ from Black Scholes Theta when time to expiry is less than 1 day.\n\nTheta measures the rate of change of the option price with respect to time decay.\n",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:greeks"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:greeks_vega",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Vega",
      "rdfs:comment": "(Only for option) The vega value for the option. Calculated using standard Black Scholes without adjustments.\n\nVega (not actually a Greek symbol) measures the sensitivity of the option price to changes in implied volatility.\n",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:greeks"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:bids",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Bids",
      "rdfs:comment": "Deribit bids object"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:asks",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Asks",
      "rdfs:comment": "Deribit asks object"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:tick_size_step",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Tick Size Step",
      "rdfs:comment": "Deribit tick_size_step object"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:tick_size_step_above_price",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Above Price",
      "rdfs:comment": "The price from which the increased tick size applies",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:tick_size_step"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:tick_size_step_tick_size",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Tick Size",
      "rdfs:comment": "Tick size to be used above the price. It must be multiple of the minimum tick size.",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:tick_size_step"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:stats",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Stats",
      "rdfs:comment": "Deribit stats object"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:stats_volume",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Volume",
      "rdfs:comment": "Volume during last 24h in base currency",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:stats"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:stats_low",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Low",
      "rdfs:comment": "Lowest price during 24h",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:stats"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:stats_high",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "High",
      "rdfs:comment": "Highest price during 24h",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:stats"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:stats_price_change",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Price Change",
      "rdfs:comment": "24-hour price change expressed as a percentage, `null` if there weren't any trades",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:stats"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:stats_volume_usd",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Volume Usd",
      "rdfs:comment": "volume_usd property of stats",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:stats"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:continuation",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Continuation",
      "rdfs:comment": "Continuation token for pagination."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:continuation_with_null",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Continuation With Null",
      "rdfs:comment": "Continuation token for pagination. `NULL` when no continuation."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:block_rfq_trade_tape_continuation",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Block Rfq Trade Tape Continuation",
      "rdfs:comment": "Continuation token for pagination. `NULL` when no continuation. Consists of `timestamp` and `block_rfq_id`."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:kind",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Kind",
      "rdfs:comment": "Instrument kind: `\"future\"`, `\"option\"`, `\"spot\"`, `\"future_combo\"`, `\"option_combo\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:kind_with_any",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Kind With Any",
      "rdfs:comment": "Instrument kind: `\"future\"`, `\"option\"`, `\"spot\"`, `\"future_combo\"`, `\"option_combo\"` or `\"any\"` for all"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:kind_without_spot",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Kind Without Spot",
      "rdfs:comment": "Instrument kind: `\"future\"`, `\"option\"`, `\"future_combo\"`, `\"option_combo\"` (spot is excluded as spot trades are settled immediately and have no open positions)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:kind_future_or_option_with_any",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Kind Future Or Option With Any",
      "rdfs:comment": "Instrument kind: `\"future\"`, `\"option\"` or `\"any\"` for all"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:kind_with_combo_all",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Kind With Combo All",
      "rdfs:comment": "Instrument kind: `\"future\"`, `\"option\"`, `\"spot\"`, `\"future_combo\"`, `\"option_combo\"`, `\"combo\"` for any combo or `\"any\"` for all"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:only_combo_kind",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Only Combo Kind",
      "rdfs:comment": "Instrument kind: `\"future_combo\"`, `\"option_combo\"` or `\"combo\"` for any combo"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:block_rfq_currency",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Block Rfq Currency",
      "rdfs:comment": "Currency, i.e `\"BTC\"`, `\"ETH\"`, `\"USDC\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:wallet_currency",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Wallet Currency",
      "rdfs:comment": "Currency, i.e `\"BTC\"`, `\"ETH\"`, `\"USDC\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:pme_currency",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Pme Currency",
      "rdfs:comment": "The currency for which the Extended Risk Matrix will be calculated. Use `CROSS` for Cross Collateral simulation."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:currency_with_any",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Currency With Any",
      "rdfs:comment": "Currency name or `\"any\"` if don't care"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:currency_with_any_and_list",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Currency With Any And List",
      "rdfs:comment": "The currency symbol, list of currency symbols or `\"any\"` for all"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:currency_with_any_and_grouped",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Currency With Any And Grouped",
      "rdfs:comment": "Currency name or `\"any\"` if don't care or `\"grouped\"` if grouped by currencies"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:settlement_currency_with_any_and_grouped",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Settlement Currency With Any And Grouped",
      "rdfs:comment": "Currency name or `\"any\"` if don't care or `\"grouped\"` if grouped by currencies"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:currency_pair",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Currency Pair",
      "rdfs:comment": "Currency pair: `\"btc_usd\"` or `\"eth_usd\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:instrument_name",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Instrument Name",
      "rdfs:comment": "Unique instrument identifier"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:instrument_id",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Instrument Id",
      "rdfs:comment": "Instrument ID"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:combo_id",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Combo Id",
      "rdfs:comment": "Unique combo identifier"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:combo_state",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Combo State",
      "rdfs:comment": "Combo state: `\"active\"`, \"`inactive`\""
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:combo_leg_amount",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Combo Leg Amount",
      "rdfs:comment": "Size multiplier of a leg. A negative value indicates that the trades on given leg are in opposite direction to the combo trades they originate from"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:trade_timestamp",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Trade Timestamp",
      "rdfs:comment": "The timestamp of the trade (milliseconds since the UNIX epoch)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:order_id",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Order Id",
      "rdfs:comment": "Unique order identifier"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:block_trade_id",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Block Trade Id",
      "rdfs:comment": "Block trade id"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:block_trade_id_in_result",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Block Trade Id In Result",
      "rdfs:comment": "Block trade id - when trade was part of a block trade"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:block_trade_leg_count",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Block Trade Leg Count",
      "rdfs:comment": "Block trade leg count - when trade was part of a block trade"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:block_trade_order",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Block Trade Order",
      "rdfs:comment": "`true` if order made from block_trade trade, added only in that case."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:block_trade_signature",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Block Trade Signature",
      "rdfs:comment": "Signature of block trade<br>It is valid only for 5 minutes around given timestamp"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:settlement_type",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Settlement Type",
      "rdfs:comment": "The type of settlement. `settlement`, `delivery` or `bankruptcy`."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:trade_id",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Trade Id",
      "rdfs:comment": "Unique (per currency) trade identifier"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:date",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Date",
      "rdfs:comment": "The event date with year, month and day"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:timestamp",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Timestamp",
      "rdfs:comment": "The timestamp (milliseconds since the Unix epoch)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:timestamp_for_book_notifications",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Timestamp For Book Notifications",
      "rdfs:comment": "The timestamp of last change (milliseconds since the Unix epoch)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:last_rfq_timestamp",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Last Rfq Timestamp",
      "rdfs:comment": "The timestamp of last RFQ (milliseconds since the Unix epoch)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:direction",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Direction",
      "rdfs:comment": "Direction: `buy`, or `sell`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:quote_direction",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Quote Direction",
      "rdfs:comment": "Direction of trade from the maker perspective"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:position_direction",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Position Direction",
      "rdfs:comment": "Direction: `buy`, `sell` or `zero`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:tick_direction",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Tick Direction",
      "rdfs:comment": "Direction of the \"tick\" (`0` = Plus Tick, `1` = Zero-Plus Tick, `2` = Minus Tick, `3` = Zero-Minus Tick)."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:order_type",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Order Type",
      "rdfs:comment": "Order type: `\"limit\"`, `\"market\"`, `\"stop_limit\"`, `\"stop_market\"`, `\"take_limit\"`, `\"take_market\"`, `\"trailing_stop\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:original_order_type",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Original Order Type",
      "rdfs:comment": "Original order type. Optional field"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:order_type2",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Order Type2",
      "rdfs:comment": "Order type: `\"all\"`, `\"limit\"`, `\"trigger_all\"`, `\"stop_all\"`, `\"stop_limit\"`, `\"stop_market\"`, `\"take_all\"`, `\"take_limit\"`, `\"take_market\"`, `\"trailing_all\"`, `\"trailing_stop\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:simple_order_type",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Simple Order Type",
      "rdfs:comment": "Order type: `\"all\"`, `\"limit\"`, `\"stop\"`, `\"take\"`, `\"trailing_stop\"`, `\"trailing_take\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:order_state_in_user_trade",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Order State In User Trade",
      "rdfs:comment": "Order state: `\"open\"`, `\"filled\"`, `\"rejected\"`, `\"cancelled\"`, `\"untriggered\"` or `\"archive\"` (if order was archived)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:order_state",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Order State",
      "rdfs:comment": "Order state: `\"open\"`, `\"filled\"`, `\"rejected\"`, `\"cancelled\"`, `\"untriggered\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:cancel_reason",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Cancel Reason",
      "rdfs:comment": "Enumerated reason behind cancel `\"user_request\"`, `\"autoliquidation\"`, `\"cancel_on_disconnect\"`, `\"risk_mitigation\"`, `\"pme_risk_reduction\"` (portfolio margining risk reduction), `\"pme_account_locked\"` (portfolio margining account locked per currency), `\"position_locked\"`, `\"mmp_trigger\"` (market maker protection), `\"mmp_config_curtailment\"` (market maker configured quantity decreased), `\"edit_post_only_reject\"` (cancelled on edit because of `reject_post_only` setting), `\"oco_other_closed\"` (the oco order linked to this order was closed), `\"oto_primary_closed\"` (the oto primary order that was going to trigger this order was cancelled), `\"settlement\"` (closed because of a settlement)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:order_state_stop",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Order State Stop",
      "rdfs:comment": "Order state: `\"triggered\"`, `\"cancelled\"`, or `\"rejected\"` with rejection reason (e.g. `\"rejected:reduce_direction\"`)."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:time_in_force",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Time In Force",
      "rdfs:comment": "Order time in force: `\"good_til_cancelled\"`, `\"good_til_day\"`, `\"fill_or_kill\"` or `\"immediate_or_cancel\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:block_rfq_time_in_force",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Block Rfq Time In Force",
      "rdfs:comment": "Block RFQ time in force: `\"fill_or_kill\"` or `\"good_til_cancelled\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger_state",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Trade Trigger State",
      "rdfs:comment": "Trade trigger state: `\"untriggered\"` or `\"cancelled\"`"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Trade Trigger",
      "rdfs:comment": "Contains information about the trade trigger state"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger_state",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "State",
      "rdfs:comment": "state property of trade_trigger",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger_price",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Price",
      "rdfs:comment": "Price of the trade trigger",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger_direction",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Direction",
      "rdfs:comment": "Direction of the trade trigger",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger_cancel_reason",
      "@type": "rdf:Property",
      "rdfs:label": "Cancel Reason",
      "rdfs:comment": "Reason for cancellation, present only when state is cancelled",
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "deribit:trade_trigger"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:price",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Price",
      "rdfs:comment": "Price in base currency"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:open_order_price",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Open Order Price",
      "rdfs:comment": "Price in base currency or \"market_price\" in case of open trigger market orders"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:quote_price",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Quote Price",
      "rdfs:comment": "Price in quote currency"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:label",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Label",
      "rdfs:comment": "User defined label (up to 64 characters)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:label_presentation",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Label Presentation",
      "rdfs:comment": "User defined label (presented only when previously set for order by user)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:post_only",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Post Only",
      "rdfs:comment": "`true` for post-only orders only"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:reject_post_only",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Reject Post Only",
      "rdfs:comment": "`true` if order has `reject_post_only` flag (field is present only when `post_only` is `true`)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:reduce_only",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Reduce Only",
      "rdfs:comment": "Optional (not added for spot). '`true` for reduce-only orders only'"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:api",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Api",
      "rdfs:comment": "`true` if created with API"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:mobile",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Mobile",
      "rdfs:comment": "Optional field with value `true` added only when created with Mobile Application"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:web",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Web",
      "rdfs:comment": "`true` if created via Deribit frontend (optional)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:max_show",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Max Show",
      "rdfs:comment": "Deprecated. Maximum amount within an order to be shown to other traders, 0 for invisible order."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:display_amount",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Display Amount",
      "rdfs:comment": "The actual display amount of iceberg order. Absent for other types of orders."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:refresh_amount",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Refresh Amount",
      "rdfs:comment": "The initial display amount of iceberg order. Iceberg order display amount will be refreshed to that value after match consuming actual display amount. Absent for other types of orders"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:amount",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Amount",
      "rdfs:comment": "It represents the requested order size. For perpetual and inverse futures the amount is in USD units. For options and linear futures it is the underlying base currency coin."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:contracts",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Contracts",
      "rdfs:comment": "It represents the order size in contract units. (Optional, may be absent in historical data)."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:log_amount",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Log Amount",
      "rdfs:comment": "For perpetual and inverse futures the amount is in USD units. For options and linear futures it is the underlying base currency coin."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:currency_amount",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Currency Amount",
      "rdfs:comment": "Amount of funds in given currency"
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:filled_amount",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Filled Amount",
      "rdfs:comment": "Filled amount of the order. For perpetual and futures the filled_amount is in USD units, for options - in units or corresponding cryptocurrency contracts, e.g., BTC or ETH."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:filled_amount_quote",
      "@type": "rdfs:Class",
      "rdfs:label": "Filled Amount Quote",
      "rdfs:comment": "Filled amount of the quote. For perpetual and futures the filled_amount is in USD units, for options - in units or corresponding cryptocurrency contracts, e.g., BTC or ETH."
    },
    {
      "@id": "deribit:profit_loss",
